learning_outcomes.en:
Upon successful completion of the course students:
- can select logs for building;
- can compile and finalize a log grid and edit the data with a spreadsheet program; - can use the log grid at the work site;
- can calculate and select with the log grid, suitable sill logs;
- cut whole and half sill logs;
- can check the leveling of the base or foundation;
- can install the sill logs according to the design;
- can check the diagonals of the log construction;
- can calculate suitable measures for the next log, and select suitable logs with the help of log grid;
- can determine the appropriate butt-tip direction of the logs according to the location in the corner pattern;
- can set the the scriber for rough notch;
- can cut the rough notch according to the type of the notch;
- can set the the scriber for final marking;
- adjust the scriber /log scribe;
- can mark groove and notch in the case of most common types of notches;
- can compile and prepare the necessary equipment for working on logs;
- can prepare the work environment for working on the log and for fixing the log into ergonomic and safe treatment position; 
- can use the jigs used for treating logs and prepare simpler jigs themselves;
- select tools according to the work operation they are going to perform;
- can cut out the notch and groove in the technologically proper order;
- finalize notch and groove;
- finalize notch and groove with handicraft tools;
- install the treated log in the wall, independently identify and fix hang-ups;
- dimension and make inserted tenons;
- independently determine the proper position of inserted tenons;
- drill holes for pegs and install them;
- smooth, finalize and clean completed log surfaces;
- maintain the tools used in log building;
- organize the work environment according to requirements;
- work economically in relations to themselves and environment.

